property.name: text
property.value:
This model simulates a search robot, which is trying to localize a target robot using a range measurement to the target. The motion is constrained by a map of the space, which is read from a PGM image and converted to an occupancy grid (following the ROS specification for maps). The occupancy grid is made available to the particle filter, as well as to the robots.
The range sensor is currently unaware of the map constraints, effectively simulating a range reading that can "go through walls".
